snippet.textDisplay:
I came to the conclusion 4 days ago I can either continue to be unhealthy or have a body glow up during this quarantine and I chose the second option so I'm doing the hourglass programme. Some things I have learnt so far: my hands starts sweating a lot in the middle so I LITERALLY have to stop working out and wash my hands then continue on. Another thing is that I sweat A Lot, places I didn't know I sweat maybe too much info but who cares. Also I can't do any type of plank but I am getting better at it, as in after 4 days I could hold it for 15 seconds.
Day 1- It was.. ok? As in I didn't feel like completely dying until the 10 minutes shred workout which I am kinda confused about. But planks, well that's a different situation. I cannot, repeating it, CANNOT do planks to save my life so hopefully I'll get better.
Day 2- I sweat like I am trying to fill a pool, like seriously. My arms were also hurting, I was kinda excited to do the hip dips workout because it's new but 10 minute shred thing again I found it hard, really hard.
Day 4- Again sweating, A LOT but I can hold planks better I would like to say, maybe not always correctly but i can hold it if that makes sense, as in I forget to engage my core. Ummm I also kinda have to wash my hands because I sweat so much that I start slipping when I'm doing planks or I don't know the In and Out exercise. I'm also kinda surprised I'm carrying this on, only because I really though 'oh I might do this for what one or two days' but here we are. I think it's mainly because I feel like have nothing else to do which is true cuz we're on easter break in the UK right now so no school either and also lockdown.
